python-mipp (0.2-0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Now handling "proxy" slicing.
    image = xrit.sat.load(...) will no more return the full image.
    It will return a slice-able object where data is read when the
    returned object (image) is called like:
    image[2:56, 1020:1070] or image(center, size)
    image[:] or image() will load the full image.
  
  * A logger is introduced based on the standard logging module.
    It can be controlled by environment variables DEBUG and LOGLEVEL.
    If DEBUG is set it will overwrite LOGLEVEL.
    If LOGLEVEL=NULL and DEBUG not set it will be very quiet.
    Default log level is INFO.
  
 -- Lars Orum Rasmussen <ras@dmi.dk>  Thu, 22 Apr 2010 08:34:19 +0000

